    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1967-06-22T04:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1967-06-22T04:45:00-05:00" n="88"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d88">
                <head>88. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Libya</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d88fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, DEF 15 LIBYA–US. Secret; Priority. Repeated to <gloss
                            target="#t_CINCEUR1">CINCEUR</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_CINCUSAFE1"
                            >CINCUSAFE</gloss>, and London and passed to the White House, <gloss
                            target="#t_DOD1">DOD</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss>,
                            <gloss target="#t_USIA1">USIA</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_NSA1"
                            >NSA</gloss>, COMAC, <gloss target="#t_CINCSTRIKE1">CINCSTRIKE</gloss>,
                        and <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Tripoli</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1967-06-22T09:45:00+00:00">June 22, 1967, 0945Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>297. Reference: Tripoli 175.<note n="2" xml:id="d88fn2">Dated June 16.
                        (Ibid.)</note> Wheelus.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>During audience with King June 21, I said I wished be certain he was aware
                        our reply to government on base issue. He asked what “agreement” we had with
                        government. I explained we had discussed approach with <gloss
                            target="#t_PM1">PM</gloss> and planned have preliminary talk with <gloss
                            target="#t_GOL1">GOL</gloss> soon after which I might return for
                        consultation. He commented, “The more delay the better”.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>In this context, I stressed need get base operating again. I stressed also
                        my disappointment at lack confidence in US on part <gloss target="#t_RLAF1"
                            >RLAF</gloss>. He said he was shocked by conduct <gloss
                            target="#t_RLAF1">RLAF</gloss>, including informing Egyptians regarding
                        movements at Wheelus. He had not told government yet, but he intended move
                        RLAF away from Wheelus to base which would be near neither Tripoli nor
                        Benghazi. When I asked about further development <gloss target="#t_RLAF1"
                            >RLAF</gloss>, he said it would be slow. We will give them a few
                        advisors, he added.</item>
                    <pb facs="0180" n="132" xml:id="pg_132"/>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>My efforts suggest to him we might find common basis for cooperation with
                            <gloss target="#t_RLAF1">RLAF</gloss> if they remained at Wheelus were
                        unavailing, at least for moment.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Comment</hi>: Throughout audience, of which foregoing was
                        part, King displayed relaxed relief that tough problems currently facing
                        country were, under constitution, government’s responsibility, not
                        his.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_NDD1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Newsom</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
